Real-Time Audit: Are We Using Tax-Calculator & drake Correctly?
Below is a four-step, copy-paste-ready checklist you can run after every form to verify the agent is pulling validated IRS rules from Tax-Calculator and reproducible pipelines from drake.
1️⃣ Tax-Calculator Evidence
Ensures line-level validation & calculations originate from the canonical repo.
bash
Copy
# Run inside monorepo root
git log --oneline --grep="tax-calc"   # should show commits like
# 3a4b1c2 feat(1040): import Tax-Calculator policy 2024v1.0

# Inspect generated JSON
cat packages/irs-data/schemas/1040.json | jq '.[] | select(.source == "Tax-Calculator")'
# Must return objects with "calcFormula" & "policyId" from Tax-Calculator
✅ Green flag → every calculated line cites a Tax-Calculator policy ID.
2️⃣ drake Evidence
Guarantees reproducible, incremental builds (no re-runs unless code/data changes).
bash
Copy
# From R console inside ./pipelines/
library(drake)
plan <- drake_plan(
  schema = read_json("packages/irs-data/schemas/1040.json"),
  ui     = make_1040_ui(schema),
  tests  = test_1040(schema)
)
make(plan)                # first run → full build
make(plan)                # second run → "✓ All targets up-to-date"
✅ Green flag → second run skips unchanged targets.
3️⃣ GitHub Actions Badge
CI must fail if either source is missing or mis-used.
yaml
Copy
# .github/workflows/audit.yml
- name: Verify Tax-Calculator policy
  run: |
    python -c "import taxcalc; assert taxcalc.__version__ >= '3.5.0'"
- name: Verify drake pipeline
  run: |
    R -e "library(drake); make(plan)"
✅ Green badge → pipeline & policy locked.
